# Cloudflare Pages routing.
#
# We tried `/embed/* /embed/index.html 200` first — production showed that
# the deployment was falling through to the root index.html (the new
# landing) for /embed/<addr>, causing the hero iframe to recursively load
# the landing inside itself. Diagnosis: Cloudflare Pages is applying its
# auto SPA-fallback for non-matching paths AHEAD of our index.html
# destination (or the destination is being normalised through pretty-URL
# stripping in a way that loses the rewrite).
#
# Fix: rewrite to the directory itself (no `index.html` suffix) so Pages's
# native directory-index handling resolves it without touching pretty-URL
# logic, AND keep an explicit catch-all at the end so Pages doesn't
# inject its own SPA fallback that swallows our deeper rules. Order is
# significant — the most-specific rules fire first.

/embed/*     /embed/      200
/configure/* /configure/  200

# Fallback for unknown URLs. Without this Pages auto-injects something
# similar but inserts it BEFORE the rules above, which is what broke
# /embed/<addr> on the previous deploy.
/*           /index.html  200
